  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to validate the Glasgow-Blatchford score for the stratification
      of patients with upper gastro-intestinal hemorrhage. This score is easy to calculate. It is
      mainly based on the hemoglobin, blood pressure and blood urea. if the score is zero, the
      bleeding is very low risk and the gastrointestinal endoscopy may be delayed and performed as
      an outpatient.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
