  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  To be admitted in the university hospital for a gastrointestinal hemorrhage (vomiting
             of red or black blood or melena)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age under 18

          -  Pregnancy

          -  Hemorrhage during hospitalisation

          -  red rectal bleeding

          -  No consent signed
